//strings for activity_main.xml SINGLE PLAYER MULTI PLAYER RULES 1. Player 1\'s pieces are white, and Player 2\'s pieces are black. 2. The objective of the game is to get all your pieces on and off the board before the other player. 3. On your turn, you will roll a number between one and four to determine how many spaces you can move. 4. You can either choose to move a piece that is already on the board, or you can move a new piece onto the board. 5. The middle column consists of combat squares: If a player\'s piece lands on an already-occupied piece, it knocks that piece back to the start. 6. The rosette in the middle column is a safe space: two pieces can reside here at the same time. 7. If a player lands on one of the other four rosettes, they can roll again. rule title
